---
import hourglass from '../assets/images/metaphor-hourglass-glow.png';
import { Image } from 'astro:assets';
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Remnant Inventory Monetization for Publishers | AdBunny"
  description="Fill unsold ad slots with AdBunny. One JS tag, AI-optimized banner selection, zero conflict with your existing ad stack. Start monetizing today."
  keywords="remnant inventory monetization for publishers, unsold ad space, fill rate optimization, backfill ad monetization"
>

<section class="min-h-[85vh] flex items-center" style="border-bottom:1px solid var(--color-border)">
  <div class="max-w-[80rem] mx-auto px-8 py-32 max-md:py-20 w-full">
    <div class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-16 items-center max-md:grid-cols-1 max-md:gap-12">
      <div>
        <p class="kicker mb-8">For Publishers</p>
        <h1 class="font-serif leading-[1.08] tracking-tight mb-6" style="font-size:clamp(2.5rem,5vw,4rem);font-weight:550">monetize every impression your stack doesn't fill</h1>
        <p class="text-base leading-relaxed mb-10 max-w-[28rem]" style="color:var(--color-text-secondary)">If you're running direct deals or header bidding, you already know some percentage of your inventory goes unsold or fills at a discount. AdBunny catches that gap.</p>
        <a href="/get-started" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg">Get Your JS Tag</a>
      </div>
      <div class="relative">
        <Image src={hourglass} alt="AdBunny publisher showing fill rate improvement" class="w-full" />
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="py-32 max-md:py-20" style="border-bottom:1px solid var(--color-border)">
  <div class="max-w-[80rem] mx-auto px-8">
    <p class="kicker mb-12">The problem</p>
    <div class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-20 max-md:grid-cols-1 max-md:gap-12">
      <div>
        <h2 class="font-serif leading-[1.08] tracking-tight mb-6" style="font-size:clamp(2rem,4vw,3rem);font-weight:550">the remnant inventory problem</h2>
      </div>
      <div>
        <p class="text-base leading-relaxed mb-6" style="color:var(--color-text-secondary)">Even well-optimized ad stacks leave impressions on the table: geos with thin demand, times of day with low bid density, slots outside your top placements.</p>
        <p class="text-base leading-relaxed" style="color:var(--color-text-secondary)">Traditionally, publishers deal with this using a fixed waterfall: call network A, then B, then C, in a set order, regardless of what's actually the best-paying option for that specific impression. It's simple, but it leaves revenue behind.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="py-32 max-md:py-20" style="border-bottom:1px solid var(--color-border)">
  <div class="max-w-[80rem] mx-auto px-8">
    <p class="kicker mb-12">How it works</p>
    <h2 class="font-serif leading-[1.08] tracking-tight mb-16 max-md:mb-10" style="font-size:clamp(2rem,4vw,3rem);font-weight:550">how AdBunny fills the gap</h2>
    <div class="grid grid-cols-3 gap-12 max-md:grid-cols-1">
      <div style="border-top:1px solid var(--color-border);padding-top:1.5rem">
        <div class="font-serif text-sm mb-6" style="color:var(--color-text-tertiary)">01</div>
        <h3 class="font-serif text-xl tracking-tight mb-3" style="font-weight:550">sits below your primary stack</h3>
        <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed" style="color:var(--color-text-secondary)">AdBunny is a backfill layer, not a replacement. It only evaluates inventory your existing direct deals and header bidding partners didn't fill.</p>
      </div>
      <div style="border-top:1px solid var(--color-border);padding-top:1.5rem">
        <div class="font-serif text-sm mb-6" style="color:var(--color-text-tertiary)">02</div>
        <h3 class="font-serif text-xl tracking-tight mb-3" style="font-weight:550">AI picks the best banner per impression</h3>
        <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed" style="color:var(--color-text-secondary)">Instead of a static call order, AdBunny's optimization layer evaluates real-time demand for each individual impression and serves whichever banner is likely to pay the most.</p>
      </div>
      <div style="border-top:1px solid var(--color-border);padding-top:1.5rem">
        <div class="font-serif text-sm mb-6" style="color:var(--color-text-tertiary)">03</div>
        <h3 class="font-serif text-xl tracking-tight mb-3" style="font-weight:550">one tag, no dev lift</h3>
        <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed" style="color:var(--color-text-secondary)">No line items to configure, no waterfall to maintain, no new SDK for your engineering team to integrate. Paste the tag, done.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="py-32 max-md:py-20" style="border-bottom:1px solid var(--color-border)">
  <div class="max-w-[80rem] mx-auto px-8">
    <p class="kicker mb-12">What you get</p>
    <div class="grid grid-cols-3 gap-12 max-md:grid-cols-1">
      <div>
        <h3 class="font-serif text-xl tracking-tight mb-3" style="font-weight:550">higher fill rate on remnant slots</h3>
        <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed" style="color:var(--color-text-secondary)">AI-driven yield optimization instead of a static, out-of-date waterfall.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h3 class="font-serif text-xl tracking-tight mb-3" style="font-weight:550">zero interference with primary demand</h3>
        <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed" style="color:var(--color-text-secondary)">No conflict with your existing direct-sold or header-bidding demand.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h3 class="font-serif text-xl tracking-tight mb-3" style="font-weight:550">same-day setup</h3>
        <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed" style="color:var(--color-text-secondary)">One tag, no ad-ops overhead, no engineering sprint required.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="py-32 max-md:py-20" style="border-bottom:1px solid var(--color-border)">
  <div class="max-w-[80rem] mx-auto px-8">
    <p class="kicker mb-12">Who this is for</p>
    <div class="max-w-[40rem]">
      <p class="text-base leading-relaxed" style="color:var(--color-text-secondary)">Publishers and app developers of any size dealing with unsold or underperforming banner inventory: from independent sites supplementing a small ad stack to larger publishers looking to squeeze more yield out of remnant slots without adding ad-ops overhead.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="py-32 max-md:py-20 text-center">
  <div class="max-w-[80rem] mx-auto px-8">
    <h2 class="font-serif leading-[1.08] tracking-tight mb-6" style="font-size:clamp(2rem,4vw,3rem);font-weight:550">your remnant inventory is worth more<br class="max-md:hidden"> than it's earning</h2>
    <p class="text-base mb-10" style="color:var(--color-text-secondary)">See what AI-optimized backfill can do for your fill rate.</p>
    <a href="/get-started" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg">Get Your JS Tag</a>
  </div>
</section>
